text:
Their Nynoya pasta was tasty. Serving time was bad. Its like as if they unable to cater large order in one seating hm.

Perhaps can provide option order in advanced so that people who wanna come in large group can do advanced order.

Ice Latte hits off very well. Minty coffee is enjoyable. Tom Yam seafood pasta also nice, must try. Creamy beef meatball should be left for someone with more diverse taste buds. The carbonara turkey bacon has stronger mushroom taste, not my kids' favourite. Overall, the service from order to receiving food was good. The meal may take longer to arrive. This place is situated indoors. Good for a family who wanted somw quite dining.

Food Many varieties of food available. I ordered MyCoffee Big Breakfast; all the side dishes look and taste very nice, the only downside the toast was replaced with a croissant with any prior information.
Service was excellent.
Atmosphere was very pleasant.
Got a fly flying around our table trying to share our food!
The music played with very hyper and appetising for the food.

Happy to know there is a coffee place that opens early as most places tend to open later. I tried their hazelnut latte and it was really good. Also had their big breakfast. Portion was big so it's value for money. Will return to try other things in the menu.
